                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.1 C 1/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-09T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your despatch 142, September 24.</p>
                <p>You may inform the Secretary General of the League of Nations that the Department
                    of State will be willing for all practical purposes to consider the identity
                    certificates for Armenian refugees as appropriate documents in lieu of
                    passports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
